  "description": "A dice mechanic is a rule system for resolving uncertainty in a [tabletop role-playing game](../index.md) using randomizers — most commonly dice, though some systems use cards, tokens, or other devices. When a [character](../../terms/character.md) attempts something with an uncertain outcome, the dice mechanic determines success or failure.",
